SEMA.JK", "TNCA.JK", "GTSI.JK", "PEVE.JK", "TRIL.JK", "PNSE.JK", "IOTF.JK", "MRAT.JK", "ARKA.JK", "CHIP.JK", "YELO.JK", "PORT.JK", "MAGP.JK", "HADE.JK", "IBOS.JK", "TIRA.JK", "PSDN.JK", "MAPB.JK", "ASJT.JK", "BIPP.JK", "CTBN.JK", "VOKS.JK", "SONA.JK", "VKTR.JK", "BSML.JK", "RELF.JK", "LMPI.JK", "NEST.JK", "KBAG.JK", "DEPO.JK", "IPPE.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-03T13:17:15", "title": "MNC Kapital Indonesia to Issue IDR 500 Billion Bonds in Three Series to Raise Funds for Debt Repayment and Business Development."}, {"body": "PT Manning Development (MD) divested 4.12% of PT Indonesia Prima Property Tbk (OMRE) shares, selling 121.36 million shares at IDR 412 per share, securing IDR 50 billion from the transaction and reducing its stake to 34.43%. As of November 2024, OMRE's shareholder structure consists of First Pacific Capital Group with 43.98%, MD with 34.43%, and public shareholders with 0%, with Tan Enk Ee Michelle Liem Mei Fung being the ultimate beneficial owner.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "properties-real-estate", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51910/bags-idr-divesting-omre", "sub_sector": ["properties-real-estate"], "tags": ["Mergers & Acquisitions", "Market Trends", "IDX", "Dividends", "Neutral"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2025-01-03T12:42:21", "title": "Manning Development divests 4.12% stake in Indonesia Prima Property for IDR 50 billion."}, {"body": "Analyst Nafan Ali expects Indonesia's retail sector to grow, driven by solid economic fundamentals and increased domestic consumption, benefiting companies like PT Daya Intiguna Yasa Tbk (MR. DIY), which focuses on household needs and is well-positioned to leverage this market dynamic. MR. DIY plans to expand its outlets across Indonesia, a strategy that has proven effective in boosting financial performance, with revenue jumping to IDR 3.9 trillion in 2023 from IDR 894 billion in 2021 and net profit soaring to IDR 353 billion from minus IDR 80 billion.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "consumer-cyclicals", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51904/analyst-projects-promising-prospect-retail-sector-mdiy-rise", "sub_sector": ["retailing"], "tags": ["Retail Sales", "Market Trends", "Market Sentiment", "IDX", "Earnings Report", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2025-01-02T19:10:14", "title": "Indonesian Retail Sector Sees Promising Prospect with Solid Economic Foundation and Increased Domestic Consumption."}, {"body": "On the first trading day of 2025, foreign investors ended with a net sell of 337.04 million shares, with PT Metro Healthcare Indonesia Tbk (CARE) topping the list with a net sell of around 300 million shares, followed by PT GoTo Gojek Tokopedia Tbk (GOTO) with a net sell of 173.06 million shares. On the other hand, foreign investors made net buys in PT Maharaksa Biru Energi Tbk, PT Astrindo Nusantara Infrastruktur Tbk, and PT Sinergi Inti Andalan Prima Tbk, among others, with purchases ranging from 25.65 million to 62.63 million shares.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "healthcare", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51903/foreign-shares-sell", "sub_sector": ["healthcare-equipment-providers", "software-it-services", "telecommunication", "oil-gas-coal", "telecommunication"], "tags": ["Foreign Investor", "IDX", "Market Sentiment", "Bearish"], "tickers": ["CARE.JK", "GOTO.JK", "OASA.JK", "BIPI.JK", "INET.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-02T18:29:53", "title": "Foreign investors net sell 337.04 million shares on first trading day of 2025, led by PT Metro Healthcare Indonesia and PT GoTo Gojek Tokopedia."}, {"body": "PT Pollux Hotels Group Tbk (POLLUX) sold its shares in two subsidiaries, PT Aman Berkat Cemerlang and PT Batam Bintang Bahana, for IDR249 million and IDR99 million, respectively, to focus on working capital and business development. The company's total equity stood at IDR2.01 trillion as of September 2024, up from IDR2 trillion in the same period in 2023.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "properties-real-estate", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51901/poli-sells-shares-subsidiaries", "sub_sector": ["properties-real-estate"], "tags": ["Mergers & Acquisitions", "Market Trends", "IDX", "Financial Ratios", "Balance Sheets", "Neutral"], "tickers": ["POLI.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-02T17:04:23", "title": "PT Pollux Hotels Group sells shares of two subsidiaries to raise working capital for business development."}, {"body": "PT Madusari Murni Indah Tbk (MOLI) is merging two subsidiaries, PT Molindo Inti Gas and PT Molindo Raya Industrial, to improve business efficiency, with MOLI as the receiving entity. The company's net profit has significantly decreased to IDR 23 billion in the first nine months of 2024, compared to IDR 80 billion in 9M 2023 and IDR 94 billion in full-year 2023, while its share price has dropped 47.26% to IDR 212 per share.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "basic-materials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51895/moli-merge-subsidiaries", "sub_sector": ["basic-materials"], "tags": ["Mergers & Acquisitions", "Earnings Report", "Market Trends", "IDX", "Bearish"], "tickers": ["MOLI.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-02T13:52:53", "title": "PT Madusari Murni Indah merges two subsidiaries for business efficiency."}, {"body": "PT Krakatau Steel Tbk (KRAS) is considering an initial public offering (IPO) of its subsidiary to generate added value and settle some debts, including a USD 234 million funding tranche for non-productive asset divesting. The company is optimistic that this measure, along with its ongoing debt restructuring process, will improve its financial condition and prospect for the future.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 1}, "score": 75, "sector": "basic-materials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51894/focusing-debt-settlement-krakatau-steel-reevaluate-subsidiarys-ipo-plan", "sub_sector": ["basic-materials"], "tags": ["IPO", "IDX", "Debt", "Mergers & Acquisitions", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["KRAS.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-02T13:38:46", "title": "Krakatau Steel considers IPO for subsidiary to generate added value and settle debts."}, {"body": "PT Aspirasi Hidup Indonesia Tbk (ACES) has rebranded its 254 household product retail outlets from Ace Hardware to Azko, following the end of its 15-year licensing partnership with Ace Hardware International Holdings, and plans to allocate IDR 200-250 billion in capital expenditure to expand its network across Indonesia. In Q3 2024, Aces reported a net profit of IDR 574.22 billion, up 18.19% year-on-year, and sales of IDR 6.11 trillion, a 13.57% year-on-year increase, maintaining its position as a market leader in retail outlets in Indonesia.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 1, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "consumer-cyclicals", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51893/rebranding-azko-acess", "sub_sector": ["retailing"], "tags": ["Market Trends", "Retail Sales", "Earnings Report", "IDX", "Executive Changes", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["ACES.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-02T13:34:57", "title": "PT Aspirasi Hidup Indonesia rebrands Ace Hardware outlets to Azko after license agreement ends."}, {"body": "PT Kentanix Supra International Tbk (KSIX) is set to list its shares on the Indonesia Stock Exchange, offering 320.67 million shares at IDR 452 each, aiming to raise IDR 144.95 billion in fresh funds. The company plans to allocate 61.55% of the IPO proceeds for infrastructure development of two existing projects, 24.48% to increase capital for PT Semangat Panca Bersaudara, and the remaining funds for operational costs, including marketing expenses and project costs.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 1, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 2}, "score": 75, "sector": "industrials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51892/setting-ipo-price-idr-share-kentanix-supra-international-debut-january", "sub_sector": ["industrial-services"], "tags": ["IDX", "IPO", "IDX Composite", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2025-01-02T11:25:07", "title": "PT Kentanix Supra International Tbk to Raise IDR 144.95 Billion from IPO on Indonesia Stock Exchange"}, {"body": "Economists, including David Sumual of PT Bank Central Asia Tbk, project Indonesia's yearly inflation to increase to approximately 1.6% year-on-year in December 2024, driven by volatile food prices and slight year-on-year acceleration in rice, chicken meat, and eggs. Meanwhile, Josua Pardede of PT Bank Permata Tbk estimates inflation to rise around 1.67% year-on-year, attributed to high gold prices and rupiah depreciation, with some economists expecting 2024 to record the lowest inflation rate in Indonesia's history at 1.6%.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51891/economists-predict-december-inflation-soaring-yoy", "sub_sector": ["banks", "banks"], "tags": ["Inflation", "Interest Rates", "IDX", "Neutral"], "tickers": ["BBCA.JK", "BNLI.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-02T10:45:54", "title": "Economists predict Indonesia's yearly inflation to rise to around 1.6% by December 2024."}]